<subSubSection pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,943,969]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a Latin adjective meaning ‘washed, bathed’, referring to Mêdog (Pemako) being regarded as the ‘Lotus Holy Land’ to the Tibetan Buddhists.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
